# Project-wide standards

When editing **any file** in this codebase, you **must** follow the engineering rules and conventions defined in the project root file **`.rule`**.

That file is the single source of truth for:

- Core principles (KISS, DRY, clean code, stability first, YAGNI)
- Architecture (app/, components/, lib/, services/, permissions/, schemas/)
- TypeScript (strict, no `any`, interface over type)
- Next.js App Router (RSC first, Server Actions, limit `"use client"`)
- Shadcn UI (use Shadcn components; no custom replacements when Shadcn exists)
- Tailwind and responsive design (mobile-first, no hardcoded colors)
- State (URL as truth for filters/pagination; useState for transient UI only)
- Authorization (permissions over roles; use `requirePermission` / `hasPermission`; never `user.role === 'admin'`)
- MongoDB (lib/mongodb, schemas required, no raw queries in UI)
- Validation (Zod for all inputs)
- Mutations (useOptimistic, startTransition, revalidatePath, toast on error)
- Security, logging, env, commits, testing (Vitest + Playwright)

Read **`.rule`** for the full text. Apply it to every change you make in this project.
